================
CODE SNIPPETS
================
TITLE: Configure TypeScript ESLint Recommended Rules
DESCRIPTION: This configuration applies recommended rules for code correctness and disables core ESLint rules that conflict with TypeScript. It's a good starting point for most TypeScript projects without requiring additional setup, focusing on common bad practices and likely bugs.

SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/docs/users/Shared_Configurations.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
export default defineConfig(
  tseslint.configs.recommended,
);
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  extends: ['plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],
};
```

--------------------------------

TITLE: Configure ESLint for TypeScript with recommended rules (legacy format)
DESCRIPTION: Creates a `.eslintrc.cjs` file in the project root to configure ESLint. This setup enables the `@typescript-eslint/parser` for TypeScript code and extends `eslint:recommended` and `plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended` rule sets.

SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/docs/getting-started/Legacy_ESLint_Setup.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
/* eslint-env node */
module.exports = {
  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],
  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',
  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],
  root: true,
};
```

--------------------------------

TITLE: TypeScript ESLint Rule Configuration Type Definition
DESCRIPTION: Defines the `Severity` type for ESLint rule levels ('off', 'warn', 'error') and the `RuleConfig` type, which specifies how rules can be configured. It shows that a rule configuration can be a severity string or a tuple containing severity and rule-specific options.

SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/docs/troubleshooting/faqs/General.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
type Severity = 'off' | 'warn' | 'error';
type RuleConfig =
  | Severity
  | [Severity]
  | [
      Severity,
      // Options is the tuple type from the rule docs
      ...Options,
    ];
```

--------------------------------

TITLE: ESLint Configuration for @typescript-eslint Rules
DESCRIPTION: Provides examples for configuring `@typescript-eslint` rules in both ESLint Flat Config (`eslint.config.mjs`) and Legacy Config (`.eslintrc.cjs`) formats. It demonstrates how to enable a rule with default settings and how to apply specific options, such as ignoring rest arguments for `no-explicit-any`.

SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/docs/troubleshooting/faqs/General.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
export default defineConfig(
  // ... the rest of your config ...
  {
    rules: {
      // turns a rule on with no configuration (i.e. uses the default configuration)
      '@typescript-eslint/array-type': 'error',
      // turns on a rule with configuration
      '@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any': ['warn', { ignoreRestArgs: true }],
    },
  },
);
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  // ... the rest of your config ...
  rules: {
    // turns a rule on with no configuration (i.e. uses the default configuration)
    '@typescript-eslint/array-type': 'error',
    // turns on a rule with configuration
    '@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any': ['warn', { ignoreRestArgs: true }],
  },
};
```

--------------------------------

TITLE: Configure ESLint Flat Config for Type-Checked Rules
DESCRIPTION: This configuration example demonstrates how to set up ESLint using Flat Config (`eslint.config.mjs`) to enable only type-checked rules from `typescript-eslint`'s recommended configuration. It utilizes `recommendedTypeCheckedOnly` and configures `parserOptions` for project service and `tsconfigRootDir` to ensure proper type-aware linting.

SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/docs/troubleshooting/faqs/General.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import eslint from '@eslint/js';
import { defineConfig } from 'eslint/config';
import tseslint from 'typescript-eslint';

export default defineConfig(
  tseslint.configs.recommendedTypeCheckedOnly,
  {
    languageOptions: {
      parserOptions: {
        projectService: true,
        tsconfigRootDir: import.meta.dirname,
      },
    },
  },
);
```

--------------------------------

TITLE: Configure ESLint Recommended Rules for TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This ruleset is designed to be used after extending `eslint:recommended`. It disables core ESLint rules that are already checked by the TypeScript compiler and enables rules that promote using modern TypeScript constructs. This configuration is automatically included if you use any of the recommended configurations.

SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/docs/users/Shared_Configurations.mdx#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
export default defineConfig(
  eslint.configs.recommended,
  tseslint.configs.eslintRecommended,
);
```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  extends: [
    'eslint:recommended',
    'plugin:@typescript-eslint/eslint-recommended',
  ],
};
```

